OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F351A1777028572
OL,3,CJay Cartmell: man pleads not guilty to
OL,4,Cmanslaughter of 8-year-old
OL,6,FThursby, of Dent Place, Cleator Moor,
OL,7,Fappeared in front of a judge at
OL,8,FCarlisle Crown Court on the morning of
OL,9,FFriday April 24.
OL,11,FDuring an 11-minute hearing, Thursby
OL,12,Fpleaded not guilty to the allegation.
OL,14,FIn the dock, wearing a black jacket
OL,15,Fand black trousers, a white shirt and
OL,16,Fa grey tie, he confirmed his name and
OL,17,Faddress before speaking to formally
OL,18,Fenter his plea.
OL,20,FNo other details about the alleged
OL,21,Fincident were given during the hearing.
OL,1,W{$~k4{$k4~sjw=                 G2/5
OL,2,W/.!+.!/*%/.!+,*%/T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BBorder NewsCThis Day FReg TV
FL,352,350,120,260,000,100
PN,35103
SC,0003
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F351A1777028572
OL,3,CJay Cartmell: man pleads not guilty to
OL,4,Cmanslaughter of 8-year-old
OL,6,FA provisional date for a trial in
OL,7,Ffront of a jury was agreed - July 26,
OL,8,F2027 - and the trial was given an
OL,9,Festimated length of around two weeks.
OL,11,FJudge Nicholas Barker agreed a number
OL,12,Fof dates for the future progression of
OL,13,Fthe case with legal counsel - John
OL,14,FElvidge KC for the prosecution, and
OL,15,Fdefence barrister Hugh McKee.
OL,17,FAs Judge Barker adjourned today's
OL,18,Fproceedings, he told Thursby that he
OL,19,Fshould co-operate with his barrister
OL,20,Fand solicitors to prepare a document
OL,21,Fknown as a defence statement.
OL,1,W{$~k4{$k4~sjw=                 G3/5
OL,2,W/.!+.!/*%/.!+,*%/T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BBorder NewsCThis Day FReg TV
FL,352,350,120,260,000,100
PN,35104
SC,0004
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F351A1777028572
OL,3,CJay Cartmell: man pleads not guilty to
OL,4,Cmanslaughter of 8-year-old
OL,6,FJudge Barker said: "It is your
OL,7,Fdocument and sets out in detail what
OL,8,Fyour defence to this allegation is."
OL,10,FThursby is next due to attend Carlisle
OL,11,FCrown Court on 28th September this
OL,12,Fyear, when the case will be reviewed.
OL,14,FIn the meantime he remains on bail,
OL,15,Fwith the condition that he must
OL,16,Frefrain from having any contact with
OL,17,Ftwo named individuals.
OL,1,W{$~k4{$k4~sjw=                 G4/5
